---
name: json-lookup
---

# v1.5 Tier 5 #22 — `lookup` on Any-typed JSON

```scalascript
val src = """{"name": "Ada", "age": 36, "tags": ["math", "logic"], "addr": {"city": "London"}}"""
val v: Any = jsonParse(src)

// Map field — same syntax on all three backends.
println(lookup(v, "name"))
println(lookup(v, "age"))

// Nested: object → list → element.
val tags = lookup(v, "tags")
println(lookup(tags, 0))
println(lookup(tags, 1))

// Nested: object → object → field.
val addr = lookup(v, "addr")
println(lookup(addr, "city"))

// lookupOpt — Option flavour.
println(lookupOpt(v, "name"))
println(lookupOpt(v, "missing"))
println(lookupOpt(tags, 99))

// String indexing.
val s: Any = "hello"
println(lookup(s, 0))
println(lookupOpt(s, 99))
```
